cs.LG, cs.CE, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.SI

This paper involves the use of neural networks for predictive tasks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The specific task is predicting colorectal cancer survival, which falls under the category of computational biology (cs.CE). The use of geographical features also suggests a potential fit for the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), as well as the sub-category of computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CR) due to the use of spectral clustering. Finally, the use of predictive models and analysis of performance could also fit under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
